}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
\pard\intbl\ql
{Upon successful completion of this course, students will be able to 
build a simple economic model, find appropriate data and use standard 
econometric tools to find an answer to research question\'2e}\cell\row\pard
}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
\pard\intbl\ql
{\~}\cell\row\pard
}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
\pard\intbl\ql
{{\b
Course contents: }}\cell\row\pard
}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
\pard\intbl\ql
{1\'2e Recap of basic concepts, Gauss\_Markov Theorem, structure of 
empirical research \line
2\'2e Heteroskedasticity and heteroskedasticity robust standard errors\line
3\'2e Instrumental variables and simultaneous equations\line
4\'2e Logistic regression (logit) and probit\line
5\'2e Panel data: Introduction and structure of the panel\line
6\'2e Panel data: panel data models\line
7\'2e Introduction to time series\line
8\'2e Deterministic and stochastic trend, random walk, white noise\line
9\'2e ARIMA models\line
10\'2e Stationarity, unit root tests\line
11\'2e Vector Autoregression (VAR) and its use\line
12\'2e Error Correction Models (ECM) and their use, cointegration\line
13\'2e Vector Error Correction Models (VECM)\line
}\cell\row\pard
}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
